    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "These options were effectively disabled in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/1568. Need to investigate if they should be removed.\r\n\r\nRelated:\r\n\r\n- vscode Nvim GUI: https://github.com/vscode-neovim/vscode-neovim/issues/1370\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The current state of things is unsatisfactory: there is no longer a way to persistently enable lang-mappings in command mode (unless I missed something). It also seems inconsistent that `imsearch` wasn’t disabled in the same commit as `imcmdline`.\n\nI suggest the following:\n- remove `imcmdline` and `imdisable`\n- disable and remove `imsearch`\n- make all command-line input obey `iminsert`\n- make c_CTRL-^ behave the same as i_CTRL-^\n\nThis would make everything more consistent and intuitive (I remembered being jarred when I started using lang-mappings and discovered that they were toggled separately in each mode). As a bonus, it will let us remove the confusing prose in `:help c_CTRL-^`.\n\nThis is of course incompatible with Vim and should be documented as such.\n",
            "created_at": "2015-11-03T15:56:04Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/1708#issuecomment-153396808",
